On 1/15/2010 12:56 PM, courtney hook wrote:
  > So a thought comes to mind, as I'm about to redo my boots. If I slip
  > one cv joint off, can I put BOTH boots on for each end of the axle?
  > Will the other boot slip all the way down the axle for the opposite
  > cv joint? Courtney

Yes you can.  But since you have the thing off, it couldn't hurt to 
clean out both bearings while you have it off.  Yeah, it's a pain in the 
butt to do it, but it's well worth the hassle of having to deal with a 
knocking bearing down the road.

Mike
